title: California Fair Political Practices Commission: Ethics & Disclosure Records: Atomic Machines, Inc

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

This is a request for the following records held by the Fair Political Practices Commission (FPPC) concerning Atomic Machines, Inc (https://www.atomicmachines.com). and its Chief Executive Officer, Jeff Holden:

Form 803 (Behested Payment Reports): All filings from January 1, 2024, to the present identifying Atomic Machines, Inc. or Jeff Holden as the "Payor" of a behested payment made at the request of a state elected official (e.g., the Governor or members of the State Legislature).

Form 801 (Payments to Agency Report): All records of payments made by Atomic Machines, Inc. or Jeff Holden to a state agency (specifically GO-Biz or the Labor & Workforce Development Agency) that provided a personal benefit to an official of said agency, including travel, meals, or "educational" expenses.

Statement of Economic Interests (Form 700) Correspondence: Any records or internal FPPC deliberations regarding potential conflicts of interest involving GO-Biz staff or members of the California Competes Tax Credit Committee in relation to their dealings with Atomic Machines, Inc. or Jeff Holden. 

Enforcement Division Records: Any complaints, investigative files, or "warning letters" issued to Atomic Machines, Inc. or Jeff Holden regarding potential violations of the Political Reform Act.

Lobbying "Other Payments to Influence": Any Form 640 (Reporting of Other Payments to Influence) attachments filed by lobbyist employers on behalf of Atomic Machines, Inc. for the 2024-2026 biennial session.

Because these records are essential to public oversight of a $15,000,000 state tax credit, disclosure is in the public interest. If fees are expected to exceed $25.00, please contact me for authorization.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Robert Delaware
